1
00:00:09,967 --> 00:00:12,733
<i>Mom, please. Stop trying
to force dad and I to make up.</i>

2
00:00:12,867 --> 00:00:14,033
<i> It's not going to happen.</i>

3
00:00:14,167 --> 00:00:17,000
<i>Even if we're upset
with each other, I still care.</i>

4
00:00:17,133 --> 00:00:18,900
<i>Just leave me alone already,
okay?</i>

5
00:00:19,033 --> 00:00:20,200
<i> Please control yourself.</i>

6
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:22,000
<i>That kind of behavior isn't
becoming of a Torrecampo.</i>

7
00:00:22,133 --> 00:00:24,667
<i>Do you call Edward
"Mr. Torrecampo", too?</i>

8
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:26,933
<i>- Just call me Paolo.
- Okay. Paolo.</i>

9
00:00:27,067 --> 00:00:28,167
<i> You know,</i>

10
00:00:28,300 --> 00:00:31,867
<i>when your mom introduced me
at Torrecampo Realty,</i>

11
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,500
<i>I thought
maybe I could apply there.</i>

12
00:00:33,633 --> 00:00:35,467
<i> It's definitely not for you.</i>

13
00:00:35,633 --> 00:00:38,033
<i>We've got our whole lives
to make good memories.</i>

14
00:00:38,167 --> 00:00:39,433
<i> And I'm not going anywhere.</i>

15
00:00:39,567 --> 00:00:41,900
<i>No matter who shows up
to mess things up between us.</i>

16
00:00:42,033 --> 00:00:44,333
<i>- I want a grandkid already.
- It's too soon, Dad.</i>

17
00:00:44,467 --> 00:00:45,700
<i> You should stop working.</i>

18
00:00:45,833 --> 00:00:48,533
<i>If you want to raise a family,
you need to make sacrifices.</i>

19
00:00:48,667 --> 00:00:49,667
<i> Just like I did.</i>

20
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:51,867
<i>You couldn't even keep this
family together.</i>

21
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,700
<i>Even your spoiled brat left you.</i>

22
00:00:56,400 --> 00:00:58,133
But that's different.

23
00:00:59,667 --> 00:01:00,833
No, it's not.

24
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:03,867
Maybe Marj's right.

25
00:01:04,767 --> 00:01:08,900
Such a waste of talent if she's
just going to get stuck at home.

26
00:01:11,500 --> 00:01:13,833
You can be a modern woman
of the world, Marj.

27
00:01:17,733 --> 00:01:19,067
Me?

28
00:01:20,233 --> 00:01:21,633
I just want to be a grandfather
already.

29
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:27,800
Wow!

30
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:30,033
It's so big.

31
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:33,833
I never imagined it'd be this
huge and this grand.

32
00:02:34,633 --> 00:02:38,133
I can't believe you'd rather
stay in a condo than live here.

33
00:02:40,233 --> 00:02:41,033
Hon...

34
00:02:42,033 --> 00:02:42,967
let's not start.

35
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,000
<i> They're here.</i>

36
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:51,067
Hello, Edward! Oh my God.
I'm so happy to see you!

37
00:02:52,933 --> 00:02:55,100
- Hi, Thea.
- Hello!

38
00:02:55,233 --> 00:02:55,900
Mom...

39
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:57,933
I just came with Thea.

40
00:02:58,433 --> 00:02:59,167
But yeah...

41
00:02:59,900 --> 00:03:01,033
I wanted to see you, too.

42
00:03:02,100 --> 00:03:03,433
I miss you, Mom.

43
00:03:03,567 --> 00:03:05,167
I miss you more.

44
00:03:05,300 --> 00:03:06,733
You look good.

45
00:03:12,933 --> 00:03:14,233
Well...

46
00:03:14,367 --> 00:03:16,733
look who still remembers
the address.

47
00:03:16,867 --> 00:03:17,833
Good morning, Dad.

48
00:03:18,333 --> 00:03:19,267
We just...

49
00:03:20,133 --> 00:03:21,600
we just dropped by.

50
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:23,967
"Dropped by"?

51
00:03:24,100 --> 00:03:25,000
That's new.

52
00:03:26,067 --> 00:03:31,233
People rarely return after
being asked to leave.

53
00:03:42,433 --> 00:03:44,967
Let's eat. Come on.

54
00:03:54,667 --> 00:03:56,600
Love, is it true
that Rodriguez left

55
00:03:56,733 --> 00:03:59,467
and took our two junior agents
with him?

56
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:03,833
And the worst part is...

57
00:04:05,733 --> 00:04:08,367
that he also took the Velasco
and Santos accounts.

58
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:11,133
That's a huge chunk of business.

59
00:04:11,833 --> 00:04:13,767
Love, we worked on that
for three months.

60
00:04:13,900 --> 00:04:16,200
Love, calm down.

61
00:04:16,333 --> 00:04:17,300
Calm down.

62
00:04:18,433 --> 00:04:19,667
Okay?

63
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:22,367
Let's not let anger drive this.

64
00:04:22,500 --> 00:04:24,133
Don't panic.

65
00:04:24,267 --> 00:04:26,467
That'll just make it harder
to bounce back.

66
00:04:29,133 --> 00:04:31,700
You know what our edge
is as a company?

67
00:04:32,733 --> 00:04:33,733
You.

68
00:04:34,767 --> 00:04:35,967
Your reputation.

69
00:04:37,033 --> 00:04:41,767
You're the Torrecampo
who listens, not just a boss.

70
00:04:43,033 --> 00:04:44,000
And you...

71
00:04:45,467 --> 00:04:49,633
you're the reason I haven't
given up on this company.

72
00:04:49,767 --> 00:04:53,467
Even though we both know
I've wanted to for a long time.

73
00:04:55,233 --> 00:04:57,767
Save that speech for tomorrow's
client meeting, okay?

74
00:04:58,367 --> 00:04:59,633
Maybe they'll come back.

75
00:05:02,367 --> 00:05:04,067
You really know
how to calm me down.

76
00:05:06,100 --> 00:05:08,400
We just need a strategy, Love.

77
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:11,733
Let's not let emotions
get the best of us.

78
00:05:12,633 --> 00:05:14,367
As long as we're together,

79
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:16,767
we'll recover.

80
00:05:25,667 --> 00:05:26,733
Too bad...

81
00:05:27,300 --> 00:05:29,367
Paolo and Marj aren't here.

82
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:31,600
They're always so busy.

83
00:05:32,167 --> 00:05:35,967
At least they're always on top
of things.

84
00:05:36,133 --> 00:05:40,200
But Thea mentioned
you're starting something new?

85
00:05:40,333 --> 00:05:42,900
A web development company?
Right, son?

86
00:05:43,033 --> 00:05:43,767
<i> Yeah.</i>

87
00:05:44,267 --> 00:05:45,233
It's a small team for now, Mom.

88
00:05:45,767 --> 00:05:47,200
Still kickstarting.

89
00:05:47,333 --> 00:05:48,600
You know.

90
00:05:48,733 --> 00:05:51,733
Business registration,
basic equipment, and hosting.

91
00:05:53,067 --> 00:05:54,867
That's such good news!

92
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:58,133
I'm so happy you're building
something on your own.

93
00:05:59,533 --> 00:06:00,833
<i> I'm proud of you, son.</i>

94
00:06:02,033 --> 00:06:04,233
Do you need help getting
started?

95
00:06:05,633 --> 00:06:06,333
I guess so.

96
00:06:06,900 --> 00:06:07,833
Maybe...

97
00:06:08,567 --> 00:06:10,300
a little help with the setup.

98
00:06:10,433 --> 00:06:12,200
Of course I'll help you.

99
00:06:13,067 --> 00:06:16,300
But please, this time,
finish it.

100
00:06:16,433 --> 00:06:18,200
I know you can do it.

101
00:06:18,967 --> 00:06:19,667
Yes, Mom.

102
00:06:20,300 --> 00:06:21,767
This one's for real.

103
00:06:27,433 --> 00:06:28,567
"For real"?

104
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:35,433
How many times
have we heard that line, Regina?

105
00:06:37,067 --> 00:06:38,533
Greg, please.

106
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,667
If he wants to prove himself,

107
00:06:43,333 --> 00:06:45,767
he should do it without asking
for another check.

108
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:50,000
Otherwise, it's just another
project he won't finish.

109
00:06:50,133 --> 00:06:51,467
Forget it, Mom.

110
00:06:53,033 --> 00:06:54,900
You shouldn't have offered
in the first place.

111
00:06:57,733 --> 00:06:59,100
Hon, where are you going?

112
00:07:00,267 --> 00:07:02,867
I'll wait in the car.

113
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:05,533
Just come if you're ready
to leave.

114
00:07:05,667 --> 00:07:06,800
Excuse me.

115
00:07:07,533 --> 00:07:08,900
Let him wait, Thea.

116
00:07:10,933 --> 00:07:12,300
What a waste of all the food
Regina prepared.

117
00:07:16,767 --> 00:07:18,533
So ungrateful.

118
00:07:19,567 --> 00:07:20,333
<i> I'm sorry, Sir.</i>

119
00:07:20,467 --> 00:07:23,467
But Edward's serious
about his plans.

120
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:25,467
You know, Thea,

121
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:28,600
I like straightforward people.

122
00:07:28,733 --> 00:07:29,967
So I'll be honest with you.

123
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:33,067
This guy has ideas.

124
00:07:33,567 --> 00:07:34,933
<i> Good ones even.</i>

125
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:38,000
But he jumps
before he knows how to land.

126
00:07:39,100 --> 00:07:40,767
<i> He's nothing like his brother.</i>

127
00:07:40,900 --> 00:07:43,500
<i> Paolo takes charge.</i>

128
00:07:43,633 --> 00:07:45,467
<i> He finishes what he starts.</i>

129
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:47,633
He knows how to carry
the family name.

130
00:07:48,233 --> 00:07:49,300
In this business,

131
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,100
in this family,

132
00:07:52,667 --> 00:07:54,633
if you can't stand
on your own....

133
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:57,067
you'll get left behind
real fast.

134
00:08:02,967 --> 00:08:03,767
Shall we eat?

135
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,833
Thanks, Oscar.

136
00:08:24,967 --> 00:08:25,900
It's okay.

137
00:08:26,033 --> 00:08:28,700
Just make sure Paolo
gets home right away.

138
00:08:28,833 --> 00:08:30,867
Of course, Ma'am.

139
00:08:31,300 --> 00:08:34,367
He's changed so much
since marrying you.

140
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:36,100
Totally loyal now.

141
00:08:36,233 --> 00:08:38,733
Straight home after work.

142
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:40,800
Thank you.

143
00:08:40,933 --> 00:08:42,233
- Okay, Ma'am.
- Drive safe.

144
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:56,100
Edward.

145
00:08:57,100 --> 00:08:57,833
Marj?

146
00:09:04,233 --> 00:09:06,400
You're not with Paolo?

147
00:09:06,533 --> 00:09:07,667
He's at the office.

148
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:10,533
He has an emergency meeting
about the clients who left.

149
00:09:12,067 --> 00:09:14,600
Looks like you haven't been
back here in a while.

150
00:09:16,867 --> 00:09:17,700
Yeah.

151
00:09:18,700 --> 00:09:20,500
It's quieter at the condo.

152
00:09:20,633 --> 00:09:23,733
Less drama. Fewer problems.

153
00:09:24,633 --> 00:09:25,733
And...

154
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,100
I'm not alone there.

155
00:09:29,233 --> 00:09:30,900
Edward, can I ask you something?

156
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:32,567
About what?

157
00:09:33,833 --> 00:09:35,633
Are you sure about...

158
00:09:37,467 --> 00:09:38,433
Thea?

159
00:09:39,567 --> 00:09:41,500
How well do you really know her?

160
00:09:42,700 --> 00:09:43,633
Why?

161
00:09:44,533 --> 00:09:45,633
Is there a problem?

162
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:49,600
We weren't just coworkers
before.

163
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:52,867
Did she ever tell you
what she did to me?

164
00:09:53,867 --> 00:09:55,000
Well...

165
00:09:55,533 --> 00:09:59,767
she said you were competitors.
Selling condos and properties.

166
00:10:00,967 --> 00:10:03,700
Edward, she leaked
my scandal video.

167
00:10:05,167 --> 00:10:07,400
She's the reason I lost my job.

168
00:10:09,133 --> 00:10:11,833
She's the reason
I almost lost my life.

169
00:10:15,267 --> 00:10:16,933
Wait, what?

170
00:10:17,900 --> 00:10:19,167
Thea?

171
00:10:20,167 --> 00:10:21,667
Are you sure about
what you're saying?

172
00:10:22,633 --> 00:10:24,700
She did it to get ahead at work.

173
00:10:25,867 --> 00:10:28,533
She wanted her competition gone.

174
00:10:29,267 --> 00:10:33,433
She has a habit of tearing
people down to lift herself up.

175
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:36,033
No.

176
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:38,200
That's not who Thea is.

177
00:10:39,333 --> 00:10:42,267
Maybe she was before,
but she's not like that anymore.

178
00:10:44,633 --> 00:10:45,367
I hope so.

179
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:50,600
I just want you
to protect yourself.

180
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:53,800
Keep an eye on her.

181
00:10:53,933 --> 00:10:56,367
Edward, really get to know her

182
00:10:56,500 --> 00:10:58,967
if you're serious
about this relationship.

183
00:11:00,133 --> 00:11:02,067
I just don't want you
getting hurt.

184
00:11:12,533 --> 00:11:13,867
Hi, Marj!

185
00:11:16,633 --> 00:11:19,200
It's nice to see you again.

186
00:11:19,333 --> 00:11:20,533
How are you?

187
00:11:23,567 --> 00:11:24,867
Looks like we'll have
to get used

188
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:27,100
to seeing each other
all the time.

189
00:11:31,300 --> 00:11:32,167
Let's go?

190
00:11:33,367 --> 00:11:34,400
Yeah.

191
00:11:34,533 --> 00:11:35,833
Bye.

192
00:11:58,867 --> 00:11:59,867
By the way, Marj.

193
00:12:00,433 --> 00:12:02,200
I also warned you
about someone once.

194
00:12:02,333 --> 00:12:03,700
You didn't listen.

195
00:12:03,833 --> 00:12:06,767
And if we're judging people
by their pasts here,

196
00:12:08,467 --> 00:12:10,567
maybe Paolo's someone
you should watch, too.

197
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:16,067
Be careful in this house.

198
00:12:47,633 --> 00:12:49,467
You've been really quiet.

199
00:12:54,033 --> 00:12:55,833
Why so serious?

200
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:59,233
Is it because of lunch earlier?

201
00:13:02,433 --> 00:13:03,467
I didn't know

202
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:06,033
your relationship with your dad
was that complicated...

203
00:13:06,167 --> 00:13:07,067
Please, Thea.

204
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:08,933
I don't want to talk
about it right now.

205
00:13:11,967 --> 00:13:13,267
All right.

206
00:13:13,567 --> 00:13:16,967
So what do you want
to talk about?

207
00:13:19,367 --> 00:13:21,067
Marj talked to me earlier.

208
00:13:22,133 --> 00:13:25,300
She said you were the one
who spread her scandal video.

209
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:26,800
Is that true?

210
00:13:30,333 --> 00:13:31,533
Is it?

211
00:13:35,733 --> 00:13:36,733
Yes.

212
00:13:39,133 --> 00:13:40,733
I was the one
who sent the video.

213
00:13:41,967 --> 00:13:43,533
But not to destroy her.

214
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:46,200
Then why did you do it?

215
00:13:49,067 --> 00:13:50,300
I...

216
00:13:50,933 --> 00:13:53,167
I was worried
about her back then.

217
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:57,600
I saw how that guy
was playing her.

218
00:13:58,233 --> 00:14:00,367
<i> Hurting her over and over.</i>

219
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:04,300
Even when his wife
confronted her,

220
00:14:04,433 --> 00:14:06,233
she still wouldn't listen.

221
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:11,333
I just wanted her to wake up.

222
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:13,633
But fine.

223
00:14:13,767 --> 00:14:17,900
I know now it was the wrong way
to do it.

224
00:14:26,633 --> 00:14:28,000
I didn't know...

225
00:14:28,933 --> 00:14:30,867
it would blow up like that.

226
00:14:33,133 --> 00:14:34,567
That it would affect her job.

227
00:14:41,267 --> 00:14:43,500
If I could turn back time...

228
00:14:44,867 --> 00:14:46,667
I wouldn't have done it.

229
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:51,867
Marj said...

230
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:54,067
you ruined her life.

231
00:14:58,433 --> 00:14:59,400
She's right.

232
00:15:00,433 --> 00:15:03,167
But mine was ruined, too.

233
00:15:05,967 --> 00:15:07,767
I lost friends.

234
00:15:10,467 --> 00:15:12,767
My reputation was destroyed.

235
00:15:14,967 --> 00:15:17,200
That's why I want to start over.

236
00:15:18,300 --> 00:15:20,400
To prove I'm not that person
anymore.

237
00:15:22,133 --> 00:15:23,400
But do you really regret it?

238
00:15:23,533 --> 00:15:25,533
Yes.

239
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:32,100
Every single day,

240
00:15:35,633 --> 00:15:37,667
I regret it.

241
00:15:43,300 --> 00:15:45,067
I don't know if...

242
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:48,633
Marj will ever forgive me.

243
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:51,267
But...

244
00:15:52,667 --> 00:15:54,500
I hope...

245
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:58,200
you don't judge me.

246
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:04,267
Please don't judge me
for who I was back then.

247
00:16:06,633 --> 00:16:07,433
Marj said...

248
00:16:08,700 --> 00:16:10,400
you can act
your way out of anything.

249
00:16:11,933 --> 00:16:15,267
I don't need to prove
who I am now.

250
00:16:15,867 --> 00:16:17,900
Or that I'm trying to be better.

251
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:20,067
What matters to me...

252
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:27,400
is if you still trust me.

253
00:16:31,067 --> 00:16:34,200
After everything
we've been through...

254
00:16:36,233 --> 00:16:38,200
do you still believe in me?

255
00:17:01,800 --> 00:17:02,667
Dad.

256
00:17:10,433 --> 00:17:12,733
Dad, we're still fixing it.

257
00:17:16,733 --> 00:17:19,000
We've talked to the clients.

258
00:17:19,133 --> 00:17:23,600
We tried to rebuild
their trust.

259
00:17:23,733 --> 00:17:25,133
But honestly, Dad,

260
00:17:25,267 --> 00:17:26,533
we're short on agents.

261
00:17:26,667 --> 00:17:29,167
It feels like it's just Marj
and I doing all the work.

262
00:17:30,433 --> 00:17:32,600
Then you'll need all
the help you can get.

263
00:17:35,967 --> 00:17:37,233
What do you mean?

264
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:42,400
I have someone in mind
who could help you.

265
00:17:42,533 --> 00:17:45,233
Someone with fresh ideas.

266
00:17:45,367 --> 00:17:48,367
Knows digital platforms,

267
00:17:48,533 --> 00:17:50,967
marketing, and online reach.

268
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:54,367
And who exactly
would that be?

269
00:17:56,367 --> 00:17:57,433
Don't worry.

270
00:17:58,200 --> 00:18:00,333
I think you'll actually
like this one.

271
00:18:00,467 --> 00:18:02,067
Your mom does, too.

272
00:18:13,633 --> 00:18:15,033
Is there a problem?

273
00:18:15,167 --> 00:18:17,800
What? Did we lose
another client?

274
00:18:18,967 --> 00:18:19,867
No.

275
00:18:20,433 --> 00:18:21,800
We just...

276
00:18:23,233 --> 00:18:26,633
have someone helping us
win them back.

277
00:18:28,133 --> 00:18:28,967
Love...

278
00:18:29,667 --> 00:18:33,467
I want you to know that
this was dad's decision.

279
00:18:34,100 --> 00:18:36,433
And I didn't want you hearing it
from someone else.

280
00:18:37,867 --> 00:18:39,633
Hearing what, exactly?

281
00:18:40,333 --> 00:18:42,033
Who's this person
dad recommended?

282
00:18:42,167 --> 00:18:44,033
Can they really help us?

283
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:49,533
Hi, Paolo!

284
00:18:51,100 --> 00:18:53,467
Sorry, I didn't know
you had a meeting.

285
00:18:57,933 --> 00:18:59,667
What is she doing here?

286
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:03,600
Perfect timing.

287
00:19:03,733 --> 00:19:06,700
I'll explain.

288
00:19:10,267 --> 00:19:15,267
Starting today, I'll be
joining Torrecampo Realty.

289
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:19,300
Uncle Greg and Aunt Reg thought

290
00:19:19,433 --> 00:19:24,167
I could help with digital
marketing and client retention.

291
00:19:24,300 --> 00:19:27,100
They said the company
could use some fresh ideas.

292
00:19:31,533 --> 00:19:33,000
Marj...

293
00:19:33,833 --> 00:19:36,033
we're working together again.

294
00:19:37,733 --> 00:19:40,333
And I'll be working
closely with you and...

295
00:19:49,467 --> 00:19:51,033
Oh, come on, Marj.

296
00:19:52,067 --> 00:19:53,567
Don't worry.

297
00:19:53,967 --> 00:19:57,600
I'll make sure to keep things
strictly professional.

298
00:20:03,400 --> 00:20:04,500
Uncle Greg offered it

299
00:20:04,633 --> 00:20:07,467
after you walked out
during lunch last time.

300
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:09,433
That happened fast.

301
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:12,400
And you weren't even
going to tell me?

302
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:16,367
I just wanted to make sure
it pushed through.

303
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:18,833
I was going to tell you.

304
00:20:18,967 --> 00:20:21,567
You should've talked to me
first before saying yes!

305
00:20:22,167 --> 00:20:23,467
Why are you keeping things
from me?

306
00:20:27,067 --> 00:20:27,833
Oh?

307
00:20:28,367 --> 00:20:30,600
Like how you kept it from me

308
00:20:31,267 --> 00:20:33,633
that your dad thinks
so little of you?

309
00:20:34,333 --> 00:20:36,733
You made me believe you chose
to leave when the truth is,

310
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:39,033
your dad kicked you out.

311
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:43,633
I left the company for a reason.

312
00:20:43,767 --> 00:20:46,833
And since you're my girlfriend,
you shouldn't go back there.

313
00:20:48,467 --> 00:20:49,667
Edward...

314
00:20:50,967 --> 00:20:53,533
this isn't about you
or your dad.

315
00:20:54,933 --> 00:20:57,200
I just want to be closer
to your family.

316
00:20:59,367 --> 00:21:01,933
This is also my chance to help
fix things between you and them.

317
00:21:03,267 --> 00:21:05,500
You've been avoiding them
for too long.

318
00:21:07,633 --> 00:21:09,667
Did mom put you up to this?

319
00:21:12,033 --> 00:21:13,267
Maybe.

320
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:13,967
But...

321
00:21:14,967 --> 00:21:17,067
I wanted this, too.

322
00:21:18,167 --> 00:21:21,767
Don't you like that your family
trusts me this much?

323
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:22,833
And one more thing,

324
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:25,933
this is my chance
to fix things with Marj.

325
00:21:26,533 --> 00:21:28,567
I know she still hates me,
but...

326
00:21:29,367 --> 00:21:31,567
I want to show her
I've changed.

327
00:21:32,867 --> 00:21:34,633
That's what you want too, right?

328
00:21:35,500 --> 00:21:36,800
For us to get along?

329
00:21:38,033 --> 00:21:40,800
I don't know
if you're doing this for me...

330
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:42,700
or for yourself.

331
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:45,133
For us, Hon.

332
00:21:46,433 --> 00:21:49,600
Everything I'm doing is for us.

333
00:22:03,567 --> 00:22:05,767
I just wanted to personally
check in on you, Mr. Orbos.

334
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:08,533
And I want you to know

335
00:22:08,667 --> 00:22:11,467
that we've improved
our client management system.

336
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:14,100
We'd really love to continue
our partnership.

337
00:22:14,233 --> 00:22:16,833
I appreciate the gesture, Paolo.

338
00:22:17,133 --> 00:22:19,167
But I've already signed
with another firm.

339
00:22:20,533 --> 00:22:22,200
It's nothing personal.

340
00:22:23,233 --> 00:22:25,567
You know how
this industry works.

341
00:22:27,667 --> 00:22:29,800
<i> Of course, Sir. We understand.</i>

342
00:22:30,767 --> 00:22:33,800
I hope you'll still consider us
for future projects.

343
00:22:35,833 --> 00:22:37,967
You've both been great
to work with.

344
00:22:38,100 --> 00:22:41,267
But I gave my word
to your former agent.

345
00:22:42,367 --> 00:22:43,733
We go way back.

346
00:22:44,400 --> 00:22:46,067
Friendship before business.

347
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:47,733
You know how it is.

348
00:22:55,667 --> 00:22:57,400
Thank you, Sir.
No hard feelings.

349
00:22:57,533 --> 00:22:59,967
And thank you
for trusting us in the past.

350
00:23:00,967 --> 00:23:01,733
I'll go ahead.

351
00:23:13,333 --> 00:23:15,133
Love, that's a loss.

352
00:23:15,267 --> 00:23:18,900
A major account is gone
just like that.

353
00:23:22,367 --> 00:23:24,200
Out of all our clients,

354
00:23:25,067 --> 00:23:27,233
Mr. Orbos is the hardest
to win back.

355
00:23:28,567 --> 00:23:31,033
He and the agent who left us
were really close.

356
00:23:32,067 --> 00:23:33,267
Like brothers.

357
00:23:34,300 --> 00:23:35,833
There's no breaking that bond.

358
00:23:37,433 --> 00:23:38,867
So, we're giving up on Orbos?

359
00:23:41,067 --> 00:23:41,900
For now...

360
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:44,500
yes.

361
00:23:45,567 --> 00:23:46,900
We'll win the others back.

362
00:23:49,867 --> 00:23:53,367
If only there were a way
to earn his trust again.

363
00:23:54,733 --> 00:23:55,867
If there were,

364
00:23:56,467 --> 00:23:59,200
there's nothing more
we could do.

365
00:24:14,633 --> 00:24:16,033
Mr. Orbos?

366
00:24:17,967 --> 00:24:19,667
Small world.

367
00:24:20,333 --> 00:24:22,400
Thea Villareal, right?

368
00:24:25,467 --> 00:24:28,267
You're with Torrecampo Realty
now, aren't you?

369
00:24:28,867 --> 00:24:30,700
Yes, Sir. That's right.

370
00:24:31,133 --> 00:24:33,667
I heard you met Paolo
and Marj earlier.

371
00:24:34,633 --> 00:24:35,867
I did.

372
00:24:36,100 --> 00:24:37,933
I already told them my decision.

373
00:24:38,600 --> 00:24:40,300
I'm friends
with their former agent,

374
00:24:40,433 --> 00:24:41,967
the one who moved firms.

375
00:24:42,633 --> 00:24:43,833
I don't want
to complicate things.

376
00:24:44,867 --> 00:24:47,067
I understand, Sir.

377
00:24:47,533 --> 00:24:49,333
But as they say,

378
00:24:49,967 --> 00:24:51,833
every client has a number.

379
00:24:52,367 --> 00:24:55,600
And I'm very good at helping
people find the best deal.

380
00:24:57,900 --> 00:25:02,200
And what kind of approach
are we talking about?

381
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:05,633
The kind that closes contracts.

382
00:25:06,733 --> 00:25:08,500
Let me make you an offer, Sir.

383
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:11,967
Better property. Better terms.

384
00:25:12,700 --> 00:25:14,300
I can make this work for you.

385
00:25:14,933 --> 00:25:15,733
I promise,

386
00:25:16,233 --> 00:25:17,867
I'll make you seal the deal.

387
00:25:19,733 --> 00:25:21,000
I know something else...

388
00:25:22,267 --> 00:25:25,600
that could seal the deal...

389
00:25:25,733 --> 00:25:27,033
faster.

390
00:25:30,267 --> 00:25:33,733
Sir, I'm sorry, but let's keep
this professional.

391
00:25:34,833 --> 00:25:36,433
You know how this game works.

392
00:25:39,567 --> 00:25:40,467
Your choice.

393
00:25:43,267 --> 00:25:44,600
Top floor.

394
00:25:47,267 --> 00:25:49,067
You'll figure out the rest.

395
00:26:08,500 --> 00:26:09,933
I really admire women

396
00:26:10,067 --> 00:26:12,733
who walk into a room
with charm and grace.

397
00:26:12,867 --> 00:26:18,067
Not the kind who react right
away or bring chaos with them.

398
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:19,933
Marj, are you okay?

399
00:26:20,067 --> 00:26:21,467
I just wanted to say

400
00:26:21,600 --> 00:26:26,000
not take it to heart whatever
Aunt Regina said earlier.

401
00:26:26,133 --> 00:26:26,967
You know how she is.

402
00:26:27,100 --> 00:26:29,333
Please, Thea. Stop pretending.

403
00:26:29,467 --> 00:26:31,367
And stop acting like
you're the nice one.

404
00:26:31,500 --> 00:26:33,367
I don't need you defending me.

405
00:26:34,767 --> 00:26:36,133
Marj, you're bleeding!

406
00:26:36,267 --> 00:26:37,900
We need to get you
to the hospital!
